engineDB::__construct()

Description
    engineDB::__construct(string $user, string $passwd, string $server, int $port, string $db)
    engineDB's constructor.  Sets a number of class variables equal to the parameters passed to it.  Connects to the database if username, password, and 
    database are provided.

Parameters
    user
	String value containing a username.
    passwd
	String containing a password value.
    server
	String containing the MySQL server address.
    port
	String containing the MySQL server port.
    db
	String containing a valid MySQL database name.
    
Examples
    <?php
	...
	$engineDB = new engineDB($engineVars['mysql']['username'],$engineVars['mysql']['password'],$engineVars['mysql']['server'],$engineVars['mysql']
	['port'],$engineVars['logDB']);
	...
    ?>

See Also
    engineDB::__destruct()
